  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Kali114-kilavi">iḵtu "āṅkataṉ puṟattup puraipaṭa vanta maṟuttaloṭu tokaii" (to.po.107) eṉpatu, "avaṉ varaivu vēṇṭiṉa iṭattu avvaraivu puṟattatākiya vaḻit talaivi taṉṉuyarvu uṇṭākat tōṉṟiya maṟutta-lōṭē muṟkūṟiyavaṟṟait tokuttu" eṉṟu poruḷ kūṟi, "ataṉ puṟameṉavē ataṟku ayalākiya notumalar varaivāyiṟṟu" eṉṟām; uyarvu kuṭippiṟappuṅ kaṟpum; ataṟkēṟpap piṟar varaivu maṟuttut talaivaṉ varaiyumāṟu nī kūṟeṉat tōḻikkuk kūṟiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en"/>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali114">
                <l>vāri neṟippaṭ ṭirumpuṟan tāaḻnta </l>
                <l>vōrip putalva ṉaḻutaṉa ṉeṉpavō vōrum </l>
                <l>putuva malartaii yemareṉ peyarāl </l>
                <l>vatuvai yayarvāraik kaṇṭu matiyaṟiyā </l>
                <l>vēḻaiyai yeṉṟakala nakkuvan tīyāynī </l>
                <l>tōḻi yavaṉuḻaic ceṉṟu; </l>
                <l rend="space">ceṉṟiyā ṉaṟivēṉ kūṟuka māṟṟiṉi;</l>
                <l rend="space">collaṟiyāp pētai maṭavaimaṟ ṟellā </l>
                <l>niṉakkorūu maṟṟeṉ ṟakalakala nīṭiṉṟu </l>
                <l>niṉakku varuvatāk kāṇpā yaṉaittākac </l>
                <l>colliya collum viyaṅkoḷak kūṟu; </l>
                <l rend="space">tarumaṇaṟ ṟāḻappey tilpūva lūṭṭi </l>
                <l>yerumaip peṭaiyō ṭemarīṅ kayarum </l>
                <l>perumaṇa mellān taṉittē yoḻiya </l>
                <l>varimaṇaṉ muṉṟuṟaic ciṟṟil puṉainta </l>
                <l>tirunuta lāyattār tammuṭ puṇarnta </l>
                <l>vorumaṇan tāṉaṟiyu māyi ṉeṉaittun </l>
                <l>terumaral kaiviṭ ṭirukkō valarnta </l>
                <l>virinī ruṭukkai yulakam peṟiṉu </l>
                <l>maruneṟi yāyar makaḷirk </l>
                <l>kirumaṇaṅ kūṭuta lilliyal paṉṟē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l corresp="2a-c">Will they say “the son cried, with hair</l>
                <l corresp="1">that hangs down [his] dark back, combed [and] arranged”?</l>
                <l>Saying “wretch whose mind does not know after seeing our people </l>
                <l>tying flowers that are new [and] preparing a wedding </l>
                <l corresp="3-5">in my name” you please come [back] smiling widely,</l>
                <l corresp="6">friend, having gone to him.</l>
                <l corresp="7">Having gone, I know. Let [him] come here with a reply now.</l>
                <l>A foolish ignorant girl you are who does not know words. Hey,</l>
                <l>depart, thinking for you it is renounced. If you depart it won’t be long.</l>
                <l>You will see [it] as something coming to you. Since it is thus,</l>
                <l corresp="8-11">when you take the order that say you may speak, talk.</l>
                <l corresp="14">So that all the great marriages stay behind all alone</l>
                <l corresp="13">in which our people are engaged here, with a buffalo and [its] cow,</l>
                <l corresp="12">pouring so that it falls down the sand brought [and] dying the house with red earth,</l>
                <l corresp="17a-c">if he knew the one marriage</l>
                <l corresp="16">that was performed among the mates with brilliant foreheads</l>
                <l corresp="15">who fashioned the little houses by the front ghat in the lined sand,</l>
                <l corresp="17d-18c">would I let go of any perturbation?</l>
                <l corresp="18d-19">Even if it were to obtain the blooming world whose garment is the vast water,</l>
                <l corresp="20">for the girls of the cowherders with a difficult path</l>
                <l corresp="21">it is not the nature of the house to join in two marriages.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
